VIM:

to avoid indents while pasting
:set paste
:set nopaste

<Leader> = \
\r - run
\b - breakpoint
K - documentation
:Pydoc <func> documentation


e -> end of word
H -> top
M -> middle
L -> bottom
J -> remove newline

zo -> open fold
zc -> close fold
zO -> open all lvls
zC -> close all
zR -> open all folds
zM -> close all folds


z. -> center
zt -> top
zb -> bottom

Ctrl-o -> last cursor
Ctrl-i -> next cursor

*-> next match cursr
#-> prev match cursr

bd -> close buffer
ls -> list buffers

F1: Vim help
F2: Dir Tree (Vexplore)
   - P to open in last win horiz
   - v to open vertical split
F3: Object list
F4: Task list

F7: uncomment line
F8: # comment
F9: % comment
F11: show this help

#i+char+ESC: insert char # times


screen:
CA+; -> all wins
CA:resize +/-N
CA| -> vsp
CAS -> hsp
CATAB -> n split
:layout save default - saves splits btwn sessions

